definition.value: An amino disaccharide that is 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranoside.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranosyl, 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl and D-galactopyanosyl residues joined together in sequence by (1->3) and (1->2) glycosidic linkages.
A tetrasaccharide consisting of three beta-D-galactopyranosyl residues and a D-glucopyranosyl residue joined in sequence by three (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A trisaccharide consisting of two beta-D-glucopyranosyl groups and a beta-D-galactopyranosyl groupjoined in sequence by (1->3) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl, beta-D-mannopyranosyl and 2-acetamido-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residues joined in sequence by (1->2) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-lactose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranose joined by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
An amino trisaccharide that is 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 6 have each been glycosylated by an alpha-L-fucopyranosyl group.
An amino tetrasaccharide consisting of two alpha-D-mannopyranosyl and two 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residues joined in sequence by (1->6), (1->4) and (1->4) glycosidic linkages.
An amino disaccharide that is 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 6 has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranoside.
A mannohexaose consisting of three beta-D-mannopyranosyl residues, two alpha-D-mannopyranosyl residues and a D-mannopyransyl residue joined in sequence by (1->2) glycosidic linkages.
